.TH "lis3lv02d_get_xyz" 9 "lis3lv02d_get_xyz" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lis3lv02d_get_xyz \- Get X, Y and Z axis values from the accelerometer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" lis3lv02d_get_xyz
.BI "(struct lis3lv02d *lis3 "  ","
.BI "int *x "  ","
.BI "int *y "  ","
.BI "int *z "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "lis3" 12
pointer to the device struct
.IP "x" 12
where to store the X axis value
.IP "y" 12
where to store the Y axis value
.IP "z" 12
where to store the Z axis value
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Note that 40Hz input device can eat up about 10% CPU at 800MHZ
